    "description": "Sahyadri Hospitals Global Group has an exciting opening for a Consultant Physician at our Tiruchirappalli office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Sahyadri Hospitals Global Group:\nSahyadri Hospitals Global Group is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Flexible working hours\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Sahyadri Hospitals Global Group!",
